info.description: Bid for valuable tiles and make the longest run.
info.ruleText:
Setup: 
Number of black tiles discarded: 3p (3), 4p (2), 5p (1)
If a player receives a hand worth less than 10 in total, they can discard it and draw another 5 cards.
  
Round flow:
Players are competing for making the best out of 21-23 auctioned black tiles, especially trying to make a long run. First player bids (they can also pass) by announcing a value ("4!"), then the turn goes to next player on the right, who can make a superior offer ("10!"). Continue until all but one player passes. You cannot bid higher than the total allowed by your bid cards in your hand. When a player passes, they get one free bid card from the compensation area, and then are out of the round until another auction starts.   

Payment requirements: Bid must follow the black tile requirement and be paid only with required A/B/C resources OR $. You can NOT mix letter resources with $. For example: Tile 10 can only be paid with $ OR any combination of B and/or C . An auction won at 8 could be paid by $2$3$3 or B1B3C5 (total 9 and you will not get change in that case).     

Game end: End game is triggered when last black tile is exposed. Scoring: Player score: - 1 point per * on their capture black tiles
- 1 point per 2 cards still in hand - 3 points per black pair / 6 points per black triplets - Sequences: 3 (3 pts), 4 (6 pts), 5 (10 pts), 6 (15 pts), 7 (21 pts), 8 (28 pts), 9 (36 pts), 10 (45 pts) Each player can discard one (and only one) black duplicate to convert it into a wild. There is also a unique wild black tile. Wild can ONLY be used in sequence. For example, a player with tiles 445677 can discard a 4 to make it a wild, and make 345677. They will score 34567 + 77 + * values + cards in hand bonus.
info.helpText:
- All players take seats - Click on deal button - On your turn, click on the chooser below your seat to make a bid. If passing, drag a card from the "Pass Compensation" holder to your hand
- Bid winner drags their bid cards to the Payment holder and then drags the won (black) tile to their personal public holders.
 - Player on the winner's right clicks on the "New Auction" button and starts bidding
- The number above the black tile indicate how many cards remain to be auctioned
 - Game scoring has to be done manually

leaveRoutine.note: Count the group of cards selected in the previous steps.
